The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the existence and characterization of balanced 4-holes in bichromatic point sets. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial arguments and counting techniques, which suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The paper also uses graph theory and optimization techniques, which suggest cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some computational complexity analysis, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category.
